You could add one with just a few lines of shell and JavaScript, enough to bump the date and version automatically before every merge:

```bash
# .git/hooks/pre-commit
#!/bin/bash
# Auto‑update manifest.json with current date and next review (+3 months)

node <<'EOF'
const fs = require('fs');
const path = 'manifest.json';
const data = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(path,'utf8'));

const today = new Date();
const next = new Date(today);
next.setMonth(next.getMonth() + 3);

data.last_review = today.toISOString().slice(0,10);
data.next_scheduled_review = next.toISOString().slice(0,10);
data.current_version =
  (parseFloat(data.current_version) + 0.1).toFixed(1);

fs.writeFileSync(path, JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));
console.log(`✅ Manifest updated to v${data.current_version} on ${data.last_review}`);
EOF

git add manifest.json
```

This script runs automatically whenever someone commits; it bumps the minor version, updates review dates, and re‑adds `manifest.json` to the commit.  
It’s self‑contained, doesn’t touch user data, and preserves the ethical transparency built into your documentation.

